{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ea64b249-7362-4b2e-a599-28c3ee519cb4","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01U6VDM6SBje7kZUQo5zAgJj","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01WxaoutrxbV1avV2aurs3Bt","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-06b7faace34041428d29d00aa9aecaee && dotnet nuget search xunit.v3 --take 5 --format detailed 2>/dev/null | head -30","description":"Check latest xunit.v3 package version","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check latest xunit.v3 package version"}],"interactionId":"db0602ac-c38f-456c-9a25-ea9f6f699692","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me analyze what needs to change for xUnit v3 migration:\n\n1. **TestProject.csproj**:\n   - Replace `xunit` (v2) with `xunit.v3` (v3)\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 doesn't use this; tests are self-executing)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed for v3's executable model)\n   - Change `Sdk` to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (keep) but set `OutputType` to `Exe` (v3 tests are executables)\n   - The project will use `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` with `OutputType` set to `Exe` and reference `xunit.v3`\n\n2. **Namespace changes**: The `Xunit` namespace remains largely the same in v3, though some types may have shifted locations.\n\n3. **Custom attributes**: `FactAttribute` and `TheoryAttribute` are still available in v3, but I need to verify if any properties or constructors have changed.\n\n4. **global.json**: The `\"test\": {\"runner\": \"VSTest\"}` configuration needs to be removed or updated since v3 doesn't rely on VS Test infrastructure.\n\n5. **Key v3 differences**: The package changes from `xunit` to `xunit.v3`, runner packages like `xunit.runner.visualstudio` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` are no longer needed, and projects become self-contained test executables. The `Xunit` namespace persists, and attributes like `FactAttribute`, `TheoryAttribute`, and `InlineDataAttribute` continue to exist. For `global.json`, I need to remove the VSTest runner config since xUnit v3 uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead. The project file changes are more significant: switching to `xunit.v3`, adding `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`, and removing `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and the Visual Studio test runner package since v3 handles test execution differently. In xUnit v3, `FactAttribute` and `TheoryAttribute` live in the `Xunit` namespace and remain inheritable, so custom attributes should work fine. I'll need to verify the exact API changes when building, but the main updates are swapping the NuGet packages, configuring the runner in `global.json` to use Microsoft.Testing.Platform, ensuring the test project outputs as an executable, and checking if the custom attributes or retry logic need any adjustments for v3 compatibility.","outputTokens":1528,"requestId":"804D:4D1EE:730301:7A44EB:6A044D4F"},"id":"4ba6f085-60a1-4f33-8234-2bb56dc7fed4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:48.376Z","parentId":"fd6a7219-a829-4946-8de5-5cb1184bbd30"}
